plot:
The Coriolis Effect is a 1994 short black-and-white film starring James Wilder
, Jennifer Rubin, Dana Ashbrook and Corinne Bohrer, whilst featuring a 
voice-only cameo appearance from Quentin Tarantino. It was written and 
directed by Louis Venosta, whilst being produced by Kathryn Arnold.
The film's production companies were Secondary Modern Motion Pictures 
and Vanguard International Cinema
